cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.LG 

This paper focuses on the use of Bluetooth technology for multi-hop networking and data dissemination. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves modeling and analysis of the Bluetooth PHY, which suggests a possible fit with cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of concurrent transmissions and the evaluation of their performance could also be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). Finally, the paper involves experimental results and performance evaluation, which could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
